  <h2>Tower of God</h2>
  <p>Tower of God (신의 탑, Shin-ui Tab) is a South Korean manhwa written and illustrated by SIU. It has been serialized on Naver's webtoon platform since 2010.</p>

  <h3>Plot</h3>
  <p>The story follows Twenty-Fifth Bam, a boy who has spent most of his life trapped beneath a vast and mysterious Tower, with only his close friend, Rachel, to keep him company. When Rachel enters the Tower, Bam manages to open the door into it as well, and faces challenges at each floor of the Tower as he tries to find her.</p>

  <h3>The Tower</h3>
  <p>The Tower is a mysterious structure that is completely isolated from the outside world. It is said that the Tower contains everything in this world, and that it is a place where all of one's dreams can come true. Within the Tower exists a unique environment, and the people living inside are called "Regulars," while those who opened the doors of the Tower by themselves are called "Irregulars."</p>

  <h3>Key Concepts</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Shinsu:</strong> The divine water that gives life to all creatures within the Tower. It can be manipulated for various purposes, including combat.</li>
    <li><strong>Regulars:</strong> People chosen by Headon to climb the Tower.</li>
    <li><strong>Irregulars:</strong> People who opened the Tower's doors by themselves.</li>
    <li><strong>Rankers:</strong> Those who have reached the top of the Tower and are ranked based on their power and influence.</li>
  </ul>
